<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12115a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12115a">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12115a"> 115(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ 1 full moon after spring / equinox</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">La lutte <font color="green">[with the bishops of the Gauls]</font> s&apos;engagea pourtant sur une question de chronologie liturgique; mais ce fut Colomban qui l&apos;attira. / Depuis les premiers temps du Christianisme, la fixation de la f&ecirc;te de P&acirc;ques divisait les esprits et agitait l&apos;opinion. D&apos;apr&egrave;s la loi de Mo&iuml;se, la P&acirc;que juive &eacute;tait pr&eacute;c&eacute;d&eacute;e de la pr&eacute;paration ou ?a?as?e??j. Cette Parasceve &mdash; c&apos;est le terme latin &mdash; concourait invariablement avec la pleine lune, ou quatorzi&egrave;me jour du mois de Nisan, premier mois de l&apos;ann&eacute;e religieuse, c&apos;est-&agrave;-dire avec la pleine lune qui suivait l&apos;&eacute;quinoxe de printemps. <br><font color="green">[The struggle [with the bishops of the Gauls]</font> began over a question of liturgical chronology; but it was Colombanus who inspired it. / Since the dawn of Christianity, establishing the date of Easter had divided people and agitated opinion. According to Mosa&iuml;c law, Jewish Passover is preceded by the preparation or ?a?as?e??j. This <i><mark>Parasceve</mark></i> &mdash; to use the Latin word&mdash; &mdash; invariably coincides with the full moon, or <mark>the fourteenth day of the month of Nisan, the first month of the religious year, that is to say with the full moon that follows the vernal equinox</mark>.] <small> <a name="STCM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#STCM"><cite title="source">Saint Colomban</cite></a> (1905) 77</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12118e" href="c12all.htm#c12118e">VI.C.12:118(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
